  "interpretation": "At an exactly matched per-step raw negative-gradient L2 budget before Adam, the three selective taper families all improved held-out-context reward and reduced harmful-far retention relative to reciprocal-linear on 20/20 paired seeds. The non-selective global stepwise scale was worse than reciprocal-linear on reward and retained more harmful-far influence. Terminal near-useful retention was undefined because its raw positive-projection denominator was zero, so this run does not independently establish greater useful-near allocation. This is finite-horizon harmful-far allocation evidence, not a steady-state, OOD, cross-task, or universal method ranking.",
